This code is the same as above, but prints more details about memory usage. Hopefully it&#39;s a bit clearer how the JVM&#39;s memory usage behaves. We continuously allocate new objects in a loop. During each iteration, if the `totalMemory` or `freeMemory` is the same as the last iteration, we don&#39;t print anything. But if either has changed, we report current memory usage. The `‚àÜ` values represent the difference between current usage and the previous memory report.

    public static void main(String[] args) {
